        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3524703765" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7219352721037725787">If you love nature reading, don’t miss this one. It’s a classic, poetic, inspiring, and an exercise in stimulating your senses and awareness. Written with beauty, but more than that, there is a good deal of spirituality going on here. Baker treks peregrines over miles of his native England. His descriptions are vivid and full of action. No plot. No dialogue. The narrative became a companion to me for the weeks that I read it. This is the kind of book you can pick up and read a random page that r</span>
  <span id="freeText7219352721037725787" style="display:none">If you love nature reading, don’t miss this one. It’s a classic, poetic, inspiring, and an exercise in stimulating your senses and awareness. Written with beauty, but more than that, there is a good deal of spirituality going on here. Baker treks peregrines over miles of his native England. His descriptions are vivid and full of action. No plot. No dialogue. The narrative became a companion to me for the weeks that I read it. This is the kind of book you can pick up and read a random page that reads like a prayer or sonnet. The experience is truly a haunting one. I read this from my local library but this is a book I want to buy and keep on my shelf as part of my library. Recommended to all nature lovers and bird advocates. Paula Cappa is an avid book reviewer and an award-winning supernatural mystery author of novels and short stories.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7219352721037725787" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

